# Mission plan

## Mission constraints (binding)

This mission is a **simplified** variant of [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc). Unless a constraint below explicitly overrides plan-and-deliver, reuse that mission's skill procedures and **development-process.md** cadence.

| Constraint | Rule |
|------------|------|
| **PRD skill** | Always **`ad-hoc-prd`** — never **`author-prd`**. |
| **Complexity ceiling** | Master Plan **`### Complexity score`** overall score must be **≤ 12**. At **> 12** (≥ 13), stop and direct the developer to **`plan and deliver`** on **`plan-and-deliver`**. |
| **Phase model** | **One phase only** — no multi-phase delivery tree. |
| **§6 decomposition** | Master Plan **always** uses **`PR breakdown`** — never **`Delivery phases`**. |
| **Forbidden skills** | **`delivery-phases`**, **`phase-planner`** — do not spawn or run inline on any lane. |
| **PR count cap** | **`pr-breakdown`** lists **at most 3** PR rows. More scope → use **`plan and deliver`**. |
| **Implementation / ship** | **`coding-session`** and detached ship chain unchanged — same skills and gates as plan-and-deliver. |
| **Command phrase** | **`plan and deliver a single phase`** only (see **`mission.yaml`**). |

Skill paths reuse [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/) unless this mission later adds mission-local copies.

### Operations filesystem invariant (binding)

Same as plan-and-deliver: all **`.sedea/operations/`** writes from the **main hosting clone** only — see [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) § **Operations persistence (main hosting root only)** and plan-and-deliver *Operations filesystem invariant*.

### Worktree removal ownership (binding)

Same as plan-and-deliver — [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) § *Worktree ownership*; rule **20** § *Worktree removal ownership*.

### Post-PR review inheritance (binding)

Detached **`coding-session`** ship chains reuse plan-and-deliver mechanics — this wrapper does **not** own PR review-cycle steps. After **`create-pr`**, the inline **`pr-review`** / **`pr-review.py`** boundary from [plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc § Post-PR handoff](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc) applies unchanged. Do **not** restate the review procedure here; when the developer picks **`start-pr-review`**, load [plan-and-deliver `pr-review/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-review/SKILL.md) via [Post-create-pr handoff gate](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-create-pr-handoff-gate).

## Objectives

1. **Ad-hoc PRD intake** — From a short change request, produce a developer-approved Ad-Hoc PRD under `.sedea/operations/<operationsUserId>/docs/` via **`ad-hoc-prd`** (not full **`author-prd`**).

2. **Bounded Master Plan** — Scaffold and draft a Master Plan with **`planner`**, compute complexity score; **reject** dispatches when overall score **> 12** (≥ 13) and recommend **`plan and deliver`**.

3. **PR breakdown only** — On the Master Plan lane, run **`pr-breakdown`** inline only (no **`delivery-phases`** / **`phase-planner`**); cap the PR list at **3** PRs; expand PR plans with **`new-plan`** + **`pr-plan`** inline.

4. **Standard implementation and ship** — After inline **`pr-plan`** §5c **Start coding session**, the **Master Plan child lane** emits §5d **`AGENT_RUN_REQUEST_V1`** for **`coding-session`** (same contract as plan-and-deliver). Ship chain runs on the spawned **`coding-session`** lane: cut-point, deploy-walk, pre-pr-review, create-pr, pr-review, post-merge cleanup, optional plan-reconcile. **Forbidden:** redirecting §5d spawn to the Squad Leader because the leader does not spawn ship skills from §§1–7.

5. **Squad Leader oversight** — Leader lane runs planning spawns (§§1–7), tracks planning ledger, and §8 ship ledger via Mission Control host sync (same automation contract as plan-and-deliver §8 when host supports this mission slug).

